3. Selecting teaching strategies - Methods, techniques, approaches
4. Developing teaching-learning materials
5. Managing learning environment
6. Evaluating learning outcomes
7. Teacher training - Pre-service and in-service
8. Curriculum development
9. Individualized instruction systems
10. Educational administration and management

### Significance of Educational Technology

| S.No. | Significance |
|-------|--------------|
| 1 | Makes teaching-learning more effective and meaningful |
| 2 | Helps in distance education and correspondence courses |
| 3 | Promotes non-formal education through radio, TV, recordings |
| 4 | Improves teacher training through micro-teaching, simulation |
| 5 | Accommodates individual differences |
| 6 | Saves time and resources |
| 7 | Makes learning more interesting and permanent |

