## 2. Models of Communication

### Shannon-Weaver Model (1949)

**Components:**

```

Information Source 
→ Transmitter 
→ Channel (Noise source) 
→ Receiver 
→ Destination

```

| Component | Meaning |
|-----------|---------|
| **Information Source** | Origin of message/idea |
| **Transmitter** | Encodes message (sender) |
| **Channel** | Medium of transmission |
| **Noise source** | Interference/distortion |
| **Receiver** | Decodes the message |
| **Destination** | Final recipient |

### Basic Communication Model

```

SENDER → Message → CHANNEL → Message → RECEIVER
↑                                      ↓
└────────── Feedback ←────────────────┘

```

### Elements of Communication

| Element | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Sender** | Person who initiates communication |
| **Message** | Content being communicated |
| **Encoding** | Converting message into symbols/language |
| **Channel/Medium** | Path through which message travels |
| **Receiver** | Person who receives the message |
| **Decoding** | Interpreting the message |
| **Feedback** | Response from receiver to sender |
| **Noise** | Any interference in communication |

### Types of Communication

| Type | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| **Verbal** | Uses words (oral or written) | Lecture, textbook |
| **Non-verbal** | No words; gestures, expressions | Body language, facial expression |

### Barriers to Effective Communication

| Category | Barriers |
|----------|----------|
| **Physical** | Noise, poor seating, visibility issues, echo, lighting |
| **Psychological** | Prejudice, frustration, lack of enthusiasm, disinterest |
| **Background** | Prior knowledge conflict, cultural issues, experience mismatch |
| **Language** | Difficult words, foreign language, grammar errors, jargon |

